It was a low-key affair in Naivasha as residents ushered in the new year with few activities outdoors.
With police enforcing the curfew, people kept away from entertainment joints for fear of rubbing law enforcers the wrong way.
Heavy rainfall experienced throughout the night further dampened what is usual a convivial mood over the past few years.



