"The curfew rule kept most of us away and I chose to enjoy my drink inside the house," said Kinyua Kabura, a resident. 
Major incidents
Naivasha Police Commander Samuel Waweru said no major incident had been reported throughout the festivities.
"It was an almost incident free festivity...we are yet to record any shocking occurrence," he said.
Mr Waweru said security had been heightened during the Christmas and New Year celebrations.
Political, church and youth leaders called for peace and unity in their new year messages.



