Cynthia Mwikali, a resident of Tudor estate, said this has been a unique new year celebration, with no hype.
"I would be out to literally crossover into the new year but the Covid-19 has messed us up. I am however grateful be see a new year and I pray for good health for my friends and family," Ms Mwikali said.
Night church
Christians took time off to welcome the new year in praise and prayers as they attended services hours before midnight.
With some churches holding virtual services as they usher in the 2021 New Year Celebrations. 
Mombasa OCPD Eliud Monari said they were happy to have welcomed the year without incidents.
Bible Way Ministries Bishop Tom Arati welcomed the new year with a virtual service on how to conquer fears.



